File: Health Minister Zweli Mkhize. JOHANNESBURG - Health Minister Zweli Mkhize doesn't own a Personal Protective Equipment (PPE) manufacturing company. The government says claims that he does is fake news. READ: MEC Masuku to appear before Integrity Committee The health department denies that Mkhize or his family is in the business of manufacturing, selling, or distributing PPE. It is promising to take action against those who create and spread fake news. READ: Diko, Masuku to be subjected to Integrity Committee Meanwhile, the ANC's Integrity Committee's hearings investigating the PPE scandal involving Gauteng Health MEC Bandile Masuku, his spouse and presidential spokesperson Khusela Diko's husband begin on Monday. 